#!/usr/bin/env node
/**
 * generate_local_pages.js — bilingual local service-area pages for
 * hernandezlandscapeservices.com (Sycamore, Cortland, Malta).
 *
 * Usage: node scripts/generate_local_pages.js          (write pages + sitemap)
 *        node scripts/generate_local_pages.js --check  (exit 1 on drift, CI-safe)
 *
 * What it owns (regenerated between explicit markers / full files):
 *   - service-areas/malta-il/index.html                (EN, full file, @generated)
 *   - es/service-areas/<city>-il/index.html            (ES, full files, @generated)
 *   - the HREFLANG:GENERATED block inside the existing hand-written EN pages
 *     for Sycamore and Cortland (three <link rel="alternate"> tags after the
 *     canonical — nothing else in those files is touched)
 *   - the LOCAL-PAGES:GENERATED block in sitemap.xml (one <url> entry per
 *     generator-owned page)
 *
 * The Spanish copy is hand-written per city in CITY_PAGES below — it is not a
 * machine translation of the English page, and each city keeps its own local
 * angle so no two pages read alike. Every page carries a full head (canonical,
 * og/twitter incl. og:image:alt, robots) plus JSON-LD, so it passes
 * scripts/check-seo.mjs. hreflang mapping: en <-> es, x-default -> en.
 *
 * Idempotent: running twice produces zero diff (lastmod is a fixed constant).
 * Requires Node 18+; no dependencies.
 */

